		Comment <a href="#c_1713651755">12</a> by Damien
		posted on 4/12/2006 at 10:08 PM
		</div>
		<div class="comment_text"><p>I stopped using Norton AV a few years ago when I realized that most of the SystemWorks pack was a waste of time, at the same time that NAV kept *reducing* in functionality with each release while consuming more resources just so they could make the UI more flashy each time.</p><p>For a year-or-so I used Trend Internet Suite which was pretty good, but its <a href="http://disq.us/url?url=http%3A%2F%2Fvirus.gr%3ADe7sDgf4ht5Z9TCLflw-Nvb9cTM&amp;cuid=3321886" rel="nofollow noopener" title="virus.gr">virus.gr</a> results aren't the best.  I had started using Kaspersky Internet Suite (6.0 beta) and thought its virus facilities were great though its firewall is a bit odd.  We're cutting back expenses (esp geek crap) so last night I installed AntiVir 7.0 (free) and ZoneAlarm 6.1, and they seem to work well.  Neither use a lot of CPU, so give 'em a try.</p><p>I've also tried Avast 4.6, which had one very interesting feature, it could scan the system before the OS had fully loaded, before any viruses would have initiated, which I've not seen in other apps.  AVG is also quite good but I've not tried the newer v7 releases.</p><p>In a word, trust <a href="http://disq.us/url?url=http%3A%2F%2Fvirus.gr%3ADe7sDgf4ht5Z9TCLflw-Nvb9cTM&amp;cuid=3321886" rel="nofollow noopener" title="virus.gr">virus.gr</a>.  There's another site, <a href="http://disq.us/url?url=http%3A%2F%2Fav-comparative.org%3A7a2u2o8pHL2N6_5ZGlGw4wD_-Vo&amp;cuid=3321886" rel="nofollow noopener" title="av-comparative.org">av-comparative.org</a> or something, which seems ok but its ranks are very different to <a href="http://disq.us/url?url=http%3A%2F%2Fvirus.gr%3ADe7sDgf4ht5Z9TCLflw-Nvb9cTM&amp;cuid=3321886" rel="nofollow noopener" title="virus.gr">virus.gr</a> so I wonder if they've got a less complete test?</p><p>Damien</p></div>
	</div>
